    "created_at": "2024-12-30T14:55:40Z",
    "updated_at": "2024-12-30T14:55:40Z",
    "body": "Try installing one or both these fonts `fonts-emojione`, `fonts-noto-color-emoji` on Ubuntu/Debian systems. If you are using KDE/Konsole as the terminal, you can set the emoji font to one of these installed fonts. Providing the screenshot for reference. You can set the emoji font from \"Complex text layout\" tab under \"Appearance\" item of \"Edit profile\".\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b41448fc-d782-4286-bfc2-2b5540e38f11)",
